#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/04-advanced-commands.md:226
#, no-wrap
msgid "`repoquery` command\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/04-advanced-commands.md:228
#, no-wrap
msgid "The `repoquery` command is used to query the packages in the repository.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/04-advanced-commands.md:230
#, no-wrap
msgid "Examples of use:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '  * '
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/04-advanced-commands.md:235
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Display the dependencies of a package (it can be a software package that has been installed or not installed), equivalent to `dnf deplist <package-name>`\n"
"```\n"
"repoquery --requires <package-name>\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '  * '
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/04-advanced-commands.md:237
#, no-wrap
msgid "Display the files provided by an installed package (does not work for packages that are not installed), equivalent to `rpm -ql <package-name>`\n"
